ttps://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/51256.patch","merged_at":null},"body":"Added a short discussion of named positional arguments to the documentation.  The discussion is the result of [this Discourse thread](https://discourse.julialang.org/t/naming-positional-arguments-at-call-site/103526).  

I've added this to the [Methods](https://docs.julialang.org/en/v1/manual/methods/) documentation section, as I think its relevant given the immediately prior subsection [Note-on-Optional-and-keyword-Arguments](https://docs.julialang.org/en/v1/manual/methods/#Note-on-Optional-and-keyword-Arguments).  But I am open to putting it in a different section (FAQ?) if preferable.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/51256/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":0,"-1":1,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/51256/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/comments/1715371083","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/51256#issuecomment-1715371083","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/51256","id":1715371083,"node_id":"IC_kwDOABkWpM5mPnxL","user":{"login":"timholy","id":1525481,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE1MjU0ODE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1525481?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/timholy","html_url":"https://github.com/timholy","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timholy/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timholy/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timholy/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timholy/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timholy/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timholy/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timholy/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timholy/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/timholy/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2023-09-12T09:40:29Z","updated_at":"2023-09-12T09:40:29Z","author_association":"MEMBER","body":"Since one can always just use keyword arguments, I'm also in the camp of being glad we don't do things in the confused way Python does.

